articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

My best advice for anyone just getting to know Marrakech: Take it slow. You’ll appreciate the sights and smells of Medina—the sprawling market where you’ll probably spend most of your time—more by wandering down a few of the twisting alleyways than you will by power-walking your way from one end to the other. Whenever I feel myself picking up the pace, I know it’s time to seek out a bench in one of the hidden gardens or grab a table in one of the rooftop restaurants that overlook the vendors in the main square. That gives me a chance to relax, regroup, and actually enjoy this mesmerizing ancient city.

tripContent.title: Chase horizons and conquer trails across Nevada’s rugged backcountry
tripContent.description: Nevada’s wild places were made for those who move at their own pace. Wander through desert canyons, alpine lakes, and ancient rock formations, all in one trip. Whether you're chasing stars in a dark sky park or breathing deep in the high mountains, this is the untamed side of the Silver State, ready to be roamed, hiked, and discovered.

articleContent.title: Your family-friendly guide to Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: Picnics, waterparks, museums, festivals, and plenty of unexpected all-ages activities—the equation for the perfect family getaway can be tough to balance. But there’s one place that does just this, promising plenty of memories to pack along with the souvenirs. Greenville, South Carolina checks all of the boxes, from hotels with plenty of family-friendly amenities to museums with interactive exhibits that’ll hold everyone’s attention (even a rambunctious toddler). Those in charge of packing can breathe easy: the weather is great year-round—the hottest month is July with temps up to 89 degrees, and the coolest is January, when the high hits around 55 degrees.

articleContent.title: Visit New Jersey’s Black Heritage sites

seoInfo.metaDescription: New Jersey’s Black community has a complex history dating back to the mid-1600s. Over the years, the Garden State has evolved to become a place where people pursue freedom, equality, and the American dream. From the Underground Railroad to the modern Civil Rights movement, learn about the incredible individuals who shaped the state by visiting its Black heritage sites, museums, and galleries.
